%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a9d446fdaefde204fbc683b0f43e403d, type: 3}
  m_Name: D2E1_EndingDay2
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequence:
  - npcDialogueText: Haven't seen you by the stage tonight.
    buttonText: Busy night
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I was cleaning glasses, but my head was somewhere else. Looking for what
        I lost.
      duration: 8.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: You looked like you were searching for something under the tables.
    buttonText: My bottle
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I had to say it. Green rocks trapped in glass. It was my ticket out of
        my old life.
      duration: 10
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: A bottle? What was in it?
    buttonText: Not liquid.
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I wasn't looking for a hangover. I was looking for a future.
      duration: 7.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: ...was it full of rum? The good stuff from the cellar?
    buttonText: Better
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: The kind of liquid that doesn't just burn your throat, it changes your
        name.
      duration: 9
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: Don't tell me it's gin. I hate the smell of gin.
    buttonText: Emeralds
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: Raw stones. Enough to buy a house, a name, a life. Now they're gone.
        The island swallowed them
      duration: 11
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: Emeralds? Is that some new cocktail? What's the base... vodka?
    buttonText: Real stones
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: She thought I was joking. Just another bartender spinning a tall tale
        to pass the time
      duration: 10
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: You're serious? You actually had... God. That must be a lot
      of green.
    buttonText: Had.
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: Now I was just a man with empty pockets.
      duration: 6
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: Emeralds... Must be a heavy thing to carry. I'm just carrying
      my father's bills.
    buttonText: His bills?
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: She wasn't just a singer. She was collateral. Her father was in some
        bad business, and now she's the one paying.
      duration: 12
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: He worked with some bad people. When he died, the debt didn't
      died with him.
    buttonText: Mobsters
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: People who don't care who pays, as long as the account is settled. She
        was the last one left to squeeze.
      duration: 12
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: I thought I could run. But I ended up here. Just like you.
    buttonText: For how long?
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: We were like clockwork toys. The Boss winds us up every evening, and
        we perform.
      duration: 9.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: I don't know. My memory is... fuzzy. Have you looked at the
      water lately?
    buttonText: The water?
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I'd been staring at it for days, but I wasn't really seeing it. Not the
        way she was.
      duration: 10.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: No boats. Not at the dock, not on the horizon. Nothing comes,
      nothing goes.
    buttonText: None?
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I tried to remember a supply ship. A ferry. Anything. But there was only
        an empty sea.
      duration: 11
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: If no one can leave, the stones are just green rocks.
    buttonText: Still pretty
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: Maybe. But beauty doesn't buy a way home. It just sits there and mocks
        you.
      duration: 9.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: At least the air is fresh out here. It's better than the smell
      of old beer and smoke.
    buttonText: Much better
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: The air was clean. It was the only thing on this island that didn't felt
        like a lie.
      duration: 10.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: And the moon... it's quiet. I like that
    buttonText: The stars too
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: We sat there, letting the night settle. The sky didn't have a price tag.
        Not yet.
      duration: 10.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
  - npcDialogueText: Well... that's one more night down. Let's see what's left for
      the next one.
    buttonText: Until tomorrow
    hasMonologue: 1
    monologueLine:
      text: I just had to wait for the next turn of the wheel.
      duration: 7.5
      pauseAfterDuration: 0
